column11: Introduction, walkthrough of what I will be doing, Jeopardy. Meet officially Margie Smith, Linda, Doris, and Fernand. Lisa works at the front desk, Brittney works Saturday's and Wednesday's.
Morning exercises with the group. Found out Nick (peer) also volunteers. Helped set up the hot cocoa bar, learned to play Kings Corner with sassy Ragna, Tim, Anora and Lee
Played King's corner with Liem, Ragna, Tim and Agitha again. Helped partake in the wii activity.
Meet Terry. I conversed with him & learned he had been in the navy for 20yrs, traveled lots, loved dodges &  tried to set me up with the guy nurse Paul. He kept seeing cobwebs, horses & birds.

Fern worked as a clerk doing different positions. Most rewarding role was a mother. Doesn't like chocolate chips. Gladi, a stay at home mom but with regrets of not being at home enough. Louis loves pink, house known as the flower house.

Terry's wife would play football, best thrower even better than their quarterback, her aunt treated her as a slave so Terry married her. She took care of the kids, a good navy wife. Margie was a housekeeper. TB testing, Intro to the Memory/Music project.
Helped with manicures, played a card game with Fern, Lee and Anola. Started music and memory project with Margie

Organized pamphlets, Helped run Bingo Night, met two Betty's, Another Doris, Janet who seems kinda scary, Les who is turning 100. Fern won a bunch of times!, The talkative Betty said to come back and visit.
Mostly chatted and played King's corner with different residents.

Talked to Dick about his life. The most important parts of his life weren't his travels in the military, rather his family and wife. He met his wife by rollerblading. She was very flexible and willing to move wherever he was stationed.

Margie seems to have a short term memory, only tracks short conversations. She reminded me once again that her brother went to WU. Attended the piano playing by Ike Mitchell. It was sweet to see the residents sing along and know the words.

Sat with Pearle, It was heartbreaking, she was crying and in pain asking God to let her sleep. I held her hand waiting for her pain meds to kick in. Once it started to let up I brought her a warm blanket for her leg. She then began telling me about home.
Attended criminal court, did minor powerpoint edits, data analysis
They were having dinner. Found out that Terry really loves bread pudding. Went and listened to the Jone&Jones; with the residents.
Games with Lee, Ragna and Doris. It was the first time I saw Doris engage in card games.
King's ministry came to visit. I sang a few hyms alongside Margie and Gladi. Finished the music and memory interview with Margie. Started the interview with Louis. Dick shared more about his family.

Travelogue with Kathy on France. Fascinating to hear about the art and architect seen on her trip. I enjoyed more hearing about her personal funny anecdotes. Surprising to have Dick engage with the activity as he usually keeps to himself.
